<body style="margin-left: 100px; margin-right: 100px; padding-top: 260px;">

	<article class="cover-page">
		<div class="background"></div>
		<div style="">
			<h2 class="font-size-32" style=" margin: 15px 0 0;">Know Your</h2>
			<h1 class="" style="font-size: 48px; margin: 0 0 15px;">Career Interests</h1>
			<h2 class="font-size-32">Individual Report</h2>
		</div>
		<div style="margin-top: 80px;">
			<h2 style="margin: 15px 0; font-weight: 400;">Name : @Model.ProfileName.English </h2>
			<h2 style="margin: 15px 0; font-weight: 400;">Assesment taken on : @Model.CompletedOn </h2>
			<h2 style="margin: 15px 0; font-weight: 400;">Report printed on: @DateTime.Now.ToShortDateString() </h2>
		</div>
	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-1" style="padding-top: 100px; padding-bottom: 100px;">
		<h2 class="text-green text-title">Introduction</h2>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			Thank you for completing the ‘Know Your Career Interests’ questionnaire. This report reflects your responses to the behavioural styles and motivation questionnaire that you recently completed. It can be used to help you consider how your preferred approach to work, people and situations might impact the type of work you are most suited to.<br />
			The report is intended to provide you with feedback on your behavioural style, motives and interests, as well as your likely career orientations and potential fit to certain job roles as a result. It also provides you with some career planning advice. Research has shown that individuals are most likely to perform well and excel in careers that are aligned to our natural style, motivations and interests.<br />
			These types of questionnaires are not infallible, but they offer us a great starting point for developing insight that can help guide our actions and decisions. Since it is auto-generated, it is important to validate the results through further exploration and self-reflection. This is a starting point for career exploration.<br />
			The report is likely to remain valid for around 1218- months.<br />
			Your results have been compared to a group of UAE Nationals who have completed this questionnaire before. Your scores on the dimensions are therefore relative to where other people see themselves and are presented on a 110-- scale; where 1 is least like you and 10 is most like you.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			The report is split into five sections.
		</p>

		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			<strong>Section 1:</strong> Behavioural Styles, Motives and Interests – This section provides a profile chart showing your responses on the nine behavioural styles. You are also given detailed information about each with pointers that relate to how your score might impact your job searching and your future career development.
		</p>

		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			<strong>Section 2:</strong> Overall Profile – This section describes your behavioural style, motives and interests in relation to career factors.
		</p>

		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			<strong>Section 3:</strong> Career Orientation – The section offers you suggested most and least preferred role types, based on your questionnaire responses.
		</p>

		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			<strong>Section 4:</strong> UAE Government Sectors – The section shows which Government sectors you may prefer to work in, based upon your interests.
		</p>

		<p style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
			<strong>Section 5:</strong> Career Planning – This section provides some questions and space for further reflection and forward planning to enable you to consider which career path would suit you most.
		</p>
	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-2" style="padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px; margin-left: -50px; margin-right: -50px;">
		<h2 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #626262;">Section 1: Behavioural Styles, Motives and Interests </h2>

		<p>
			The section outlines your behavioural styles. These are the factors that reflect your preferred style and approach. There are nine in total and the profile chart below shows you where your own preference lies on each.
		</p>

		<p>
			If your score lies towards the extreme end of the scale this means that your preference is more pronounced, whereas those scores in the middle are more typical of most. There are not right or wrong scores as different styles suit different environments and roles.
		</p>

		<table class="career-report-table" style="width: 100%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 30px;">
			@foreach (var scale in Model.profileScaleScoreReportsView)
			{
				<tr class="">
					<td class="" colspan="4" style="background-color: #66c9c4; padding: 10px;">
						<p style="color: #fff;">
							@scale.ScaleLowDescription.Current
						</p>
					</td>
					<td class="text-center" colspan="6" style="padding: 0px; vertical-align: middle;">
						<p class="font-weight-600" style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 16px;">@scale.ScaleName.Current</p>
                        <div class="square display-block average" style="border-right: 5px solid #66c9c4; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden;">
                            @if (scale.Score == 1)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 2)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 3)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 4)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 5)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5"></div>
                            }
                            else
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5 grey-sq"></div>
                            }


                        </div>
                        <div class="square display-block average" style=" display: inline-block; overflow: hidden;">
                            @if (scale.Score == 6)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 6"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 7"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 8"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 9 "></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 10"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 7)
                            {

                                <div class="sq 6"></div>
                                <div class="sq 7"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 8"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 9 "></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 10"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 8)
                            {

                                <div class="sq 6"></div>
                                <div class="sq 7"></div>
                                <div class="sq 8"></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 9 "></div>
                                <div class="sq grey-sq 10"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 9)
                            {
                                <div class="sq 6"></div>
                                <div class="sq 7"></div>
                                <div class="sq 8"></div>
                                <div class="sq 9"></div>
                                <div class="sq 10 grey-sq"></div>
                            }
                            else if (scale.Score == 10)
                            {

                                <div class="sq 6"></div>
                                <div class="sq 7"></div>
                                <div class="sq 8"></div>
                                <div class="sq 9 "></div>
                                <div class="sq 10"></div>
                            }
                            else
                            {
                                <div class="sq 1 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 2 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 3 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 4 grey-sq"></div>
                                <div class="sq 5 grey-sq"></div>
                            }

                        </div>
					</td>
					<td colspan="4" style="background-color: #66c9c4; padding: 10px;">
						<p style="color: #fff;">
							@scale.ScaleHighDescription.Current
						</p>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr style="height: 15px;"></tr>

			}

		</table>

	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-3" style="padding-top: 100px; padding-bottom: 100px;">

		<h2 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #626262; margin-bottom: 10px;">Section 2: Overall Profile</h2>
		<p style="margin-top: 0;">This section offers a description of your own scores on each of the career factors. It considers what the score means for you, how it might affect your job seeking and your career development, as well as anything you might want to look out for that could hold you back. There are positives and negatives for each factor and this section helps you to understand the implications for you.</p>
		@foreach (var narrative in Model.profileScaleNarrativeDescriptionsView)
		{
			<div class="be-profile" style="min-height: 120px;">
				<p class="leadership-sprint font-weight-600" style="margin-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 15px; padding: 10px; font-size: 14px;">@narrative.ScaleName.Current</p>
				<p class="leadership-sprint font-weight-600" style="padding: 10px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 3px; font-size: 12px;">
					@narrative.Description.Current
				</p>
			</div>
		}
		<div class="be-profile" style="min-height: 120px;">
		</div>
		<div class="be-profile" style="min-height: 120px;">
		</div>
		<div class="be-profile" style="min-height: 120px;">
		</div>
	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-5" style="padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px; margin-left: -50px; margin-right: -50px;">
		<h2 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #626262; margin-bottom: 5px;">Section 2: Career Orientation</h2>
		<p style="margin-top: 0;">There are clear links between our behavioural styles, motivations and interests with the types of roles that we are most suited to. This section is a starting point for you to consider. It is not directive; it offers you three roles to think about as they appear to be most suited to you. However, they should not be regarded as the only options open to you.</p>
		<p>
			At the bottom of this page you are provided with some pointers regarding the types of environments that would suit you best, based on your responses to the questionnaire. This section helps you to think about how this might impact your job -search. Use this when you look at organisational information to consider whether your own motivations would be aligned with the organisational culture.
		</p>
		<p>
			Based on your questionnaire responses, the ٣ most preferred role types that may be most suited to you are shown below. Please note, this is only a guide and further self-reflection and exploration may be useful. Please use the reflections page at the back of the report to help guide you further.
		</p>

		<h3 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #6e6e6e;">Most Preferred Role Types</h3>
		<table class="" style="width: 100%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse;">
			@foreach (var leastjob in Model.profileHighestJobNarrativeDescriptionsView)
			{

				<tr>
					<td class="text-center" colspan="3" style="background-color: #00a99e; padding: 0px 15px; vertical-align: middle;">
						<h3 style="color: #fff; margin: 0;">@leastjob.ScaleName.Current</h3>
					</td>
					<td colspan="9" style="background-color: #eef0ef; padding: 10px 15px;">
						<p style="font-size: 14px; margin: 0;">
							@leastjob.Description.Current
						</p>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr style="height: 10px;"></tr>

			}


		</table>

	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-6" style="padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px; margin-left: -50px; margin-right: -50px;">

		<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">
			In the same way that there are roles that you might be particularly suited to, there are also roles that you may find suit you less well. Using your responses to the questionnaire, environments and roles where your fit is least strong have been identified. If these are roles you have been considering in the past, it is important not to simply disregard them. Instead, talk to other people who know you well about this report and do more research about the jobs listed and the types of organisations you could work within.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
			Based on your questionnaire responses, the 3 least preferred role types that may be most suited to you are shown below. Please note, this is only a guide and further self-reflection and exploration may be useful. Please us the reflections page at the back of the report to help guide you further.
		</p>

		<h3 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #6e6e6e;">Least Preferred Role Types</h3>
		<table class="" style="width: 100%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse;">
			@foreach (var leastjob in Model.profileLowestJobNarrativeDescriptionsView)
			{

				<tr>
					<td class="text-center" colspan="3" style="background-color: #00a99e; padding: 0px 15px; vertical-align: middle;">
						<h3 style="color: #fff; margin: 0;">@leastjob.ScaleName.Current</h3>
					</td>
					<td colspan="9" style="background-color: #eef0ef; padding: 10px 15px;">
						<p style="font-size: 14px; margin: 0;">
							@leastjob.Description.Current
						</p>
					</td>
				</tr>

				<tr style="height: 10px;"></tr>

			}


		</table>

		<h2 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #626262; margin-bottom: 5px;">Section 4: UAE Government Sectors</h2>
		<p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 10px;">
			It is useful to think about which UAE Government Sectors you may find prefer to work in, based upon your career interests and motivations. Within each sector there are various roles, which require different motivational interests and behavioural styles. However, working within a sector that has overall work themes similar to your interests can be useful, in terms of organisational and cultural fit.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
			Based on your questionnaire responses, below are likely to be your top 3 most preferred sectors to work in.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-top:10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
			Please note, these sectors are only an indication and are a starting point for further exploration. This is only a guide and further self-reflection may be useful. Please use the reflections page at the back of the report to help guide you further.
		</p>
		<div class="career-sectors">
			<div style="clear: both; overflow: hidden;">
				<table class="" style="width: 45%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse; float: left; height: 120px;">

					<tr>
						<td colspan="8" style="background-color: #00a99e; padding: 10px 15px;">
							<h4 style="color: #fff; margin: 0;">Sector 1</h4>
							<h3 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #fff; margin: 10px 0;">Positive<br /> & Happy Lifestyle</h3>
						</td>
						<td class="text-center" colspan="4" style="background-color: #999999; padding: 0px 15px; vertical-align: middle;">
							<img src="~/Assets/images/career-sector-1.png" alt="" style="width: 100%;" />
						</td>
					</tr>

				</table>
				<table class="" style="width: 45%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse; float: right; height: 120px;">

					<tr>
						<td colspan="8" style="background-color: #00a99e; padding: 10px 15px;">
							<h4 style="color: #fff; margin: 0;">Sector 2</h4>
							<h3 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #fff; margin: 10px 0;">International Political Relations and Security</h3>
						</td>
						<td class="text-center" colspan="4" style="background-color: #999999; padding: 0px 15px; vertical-align: middle;">
							<img src="~/Assets/images/career-sector-2.png" alt="" style="width: 100%;" />
						</td>
					</tr>

				</table>
			</div>

			<div style="margin-top: 30px;">
				<table class="" style="width: 45%; table-layout: fixed; border-collapse: collapse; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; height: 120px;">

					<tr>
						<td colspan="8" style="background-color: #00a99e; padding: 10px 15px;">
							<h4 style="color: #fff; margin: 0;">Sector 3</h4>
							<h3 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #fff; margin: 10px 0;">Human Capital and Innovation</h3>
						</td>
						<td class="text-center" colspan="4" style="background-color: #999999; padding: 0px 15px; vertical-align: middle;">
							<img src="~/Assets/images/career-sector-3.png" alt="" style="width: 100%;" />
						</td>
					</tr>

				</table>
			</div>

		</div>
	</article>

	<div class="breakhere"></div>

	<article class="page-7" style="padding-top: 50px; padding-bottom: 50px; margin-left: -50px; margin-right: -50px;">

		<h2 class="font-weight-600" style="color: #626262; margin-bottom: 5px;">Section 5: Career Planning </h2>
		<p>Consider the information in this report.</p>

		@foreach (var question in Model.ProfileAnswerQuestionGroups)
		{
			<div class="career-planning">
				@question.Question.Current
				@if (question.Answer != null)
				{
					<p>@question.Answer.Current</p>
				}
			</div>
		}

	</article>

